{
  "doc_id": "8641",
  "text": "NMAAP1 is a membrane-associated protein that contains an open-reading frame (ORF) that encodes a peptide of 555 amino acids and a small portion of the MAB-21 domain that is expressed in a wide range of tissues [CITATION_1] . Members of the MAB-21 family control cellular differentiation in C. elegans, Danio rerio, and Mus musculus [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
